    • Method Detail

      • filter

        public MultipleObjectsBundle filter(MultipleObjectsBundle objects)
        A standard implementation of the filter process. First of all, all suitable representations are found. Then (if prepareStart(de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.data.type.SimpleTypeInformation<I>) returns true), the data is processed read-only in a first pass. In the main pass, each object is then filtered using filterSingleObject(I).
        Specified by:
        filter in interface ObjectFilter
        Parameters:
        objects - Object to filter
        Returns:
        Filtered objects
